doctype html(lang='en')
head
		title Question Editor
		link(href='/stylesheets/bootstrap.min.css', rel='stylesheet')
		meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
		link(href='/stylesheets/style.css' rel='stylesheet')
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='/fonts/font-awesome/css/font-awesome.min.css')
		style(type='text/css', media='screen').
			#editor {
			height:100%;
			}
	body(style="overflow:hidden")
	#container.column
		#content.col-md-4
			h2 JAVASCRIPT
			p

			#accordion.panel-group
				.panel.panel-default
					.panel-heading
						h4.panel-title
							a(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapse1') What is JAVASCRIPT?
					#collapse1.panel-collapse.collapse.in
						.panel-body
							| Back in 1995, a developer at Netscape named Brendan Eich introduced JavaScript to the world. 
							| Despite Java and JavaScript both containing "Java" in their names, they're two distinct languages that have nothing to do with one another. 
							| The official name of JavaScript is ECMAScript which gets its name from the international organization that maintains it, ECMA (European Computer Manufacturers Association). 
				.panel.panel-default
					.panel-heading
						h4.panel-title
							a(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapse2') Introduction to JAVASCRIPT
					#collapse2.panel-collapse.collapse
						.panel-body
							| In the next few weeks, your web pages are going to go from static to dynamic thanks to JavaScript and the JavaScript library, jQuery. 
							| jQuery is a JavaScript library that makes it easier to incorporate JavaScript on your web pages.
							| To have a feel of how the javascript syntax works, type in the following code to the text editor to your right and click compile
							| console.log("Hello World")
				.panel.panel-default
					.panel-heading
						h4.panel-title
							a(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapse3') Using tags.
					#collapse3.panel-collapse.collapse
						.panel-body
							| Was that not awesome? Click next to get into the technicalities of JavaScript

		#practise.col-md-8

				#editor.col-md-7

				#result.col-md-5
					.form-group
						label
						select.form-control.languageSelector#languageSelector(onchange="changeLanguage()" name="lang" required)
							option(value="1" selected=(language=="1") ) C
							option(value="2" selected=(language=="2") ) C++
							option(value="9" selected=(language=="9")) C#
							option(value="3"  selected=(language=="3")) Java
							option(value="20"  selected=(language=="20")) Javascript
							option(value="5" selected=(language=="5") ) Python
					#compile
						#compileResponse
							textarea.customInput(placeholder="Provide your input here each seperated by a new line.")
						#compileButton
							button.compileButton() COMPILE & RUN

					#run
						#runResponse
						#submitButton
							button.submitButton(disabled) YOUR OUTPUT
					#submit



				script(src='/src-noconflict/ace.js', type='text/javascript', charset='utf-8')
				script.
					var editor = ace.edit("editor");
					editor.setTheme("ace/theme/monokai");
					editor.setFontSize(16);
					editor.getSession().setMode("ace/mode/#{langCode}");
				script(src='https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.12.4/jquery.min.js')

				script(src='/javascripts/bootstrap.min.js')
				script(src="/javascripts/jquery.js")
				script(src="/javascripts/compile.js")
